WEBVTT

00:02.827 --> 00:05.344
What do you think
of the view, Fry?

00:05.413 --> 00:07.724
It really puts things
in perspective.

00:07.793 --> 00:10.067
I mean, from up here,
an entire world

00:10.137 --> 00:12.034
can seem utterly
insignificant.

00:12.102 --> 00:13.343
[ Splat ]

00:49.792 --> 00:51.033
[ Bender ]
Hey, nice seats.

00:51.103 --> 00:53.206
We're close enough that when you

00:53.274 --> 00:56.067
knock a player down
with a beer bottle,
he stays down.

00:56.137 --> 00:57.240
I don't get this.

00:57.310 --> 00:59.792
Is blernsball exactly
the same as baseball?

00:59.862 --> 01:01.448
Baseball?
God forbid.

01:01.517 --> 01:05.655
Face it, Fry.
Baseball was as boring
as Mom and apple pie.

01:05.724 --> 01:07.688
That's why they
jazzed it up.

01:07.757 --> 01:09.724
Boring? Baseball wasn't...

01:09.793 --> 01:12.102
Hmm, so they
finally jazzed it up.

01:16.206 --> 01:17.240
Home run!

01:17.310 --> 01:18.688
[ Laughing ]
Yay, yay!

01:18.757 --> 01:20.103
Right?

01:21.343 --> 01:22.206
Ugh.

01:22.275 --> 01:24.516
[ Groaning ]

01:24.585 --> 01:25.551
Out.

01:25.620 --> 01:27.343
[ Crowd ]
Yeah! Yay!

01:27.412 --> 01:29.448
What just happened?

01:29.516 --> 01:31.551
Why is the ball on
that sproingy thing?

01:31.620 --> 01:33.861
It's traditional,
just like aluminum bats

01:33.930 --> 01:35.412
and the
seventh-inning grope.

01:39.723 --> 01:41.723
Hey, hey, hey!

01:41.793 --> 01:44.448
I got me a souvenir.

01:44.516 --> 01:47.240
Aw, here you go, kid.

01:47.310 --> 01:48.620
[ Grunts ]

01:53.137 --> 01:55.965
I'd like
a jumbo squid log, please.

01:56.033 --> 01:57.723
We don't sell those.

01:57.793 --> 01:59.033
All right, all right.

01:59.103 --> 02:01.447
Let me have
one of your young on a roll.

02:01.516 --> 02:02.724
We're out of rolls.

02:02.793 --> 02:06.793
Fine. Just give me something
crawling with parasites.

02:06.861 --> 02:09.378
[ Admiring Growl ]

02:09.448 --> 02:10.586
Hmm.

02:10.655 --> 02:12.655
At least hot dogs
haven't changed.

02:12.723 --> 02:14.550
Hey, buddies, who wants popcorn?

02:14.620 --> 02:16.620
Oh, I'll have some.Oh, yeah. Popcorn.

02:16.688 --> 02:18.550
[ Corn Popping ]

02:19.793 --> 02:23.343
Anyone want
butter on that?

02:23.413 --> 02:26.481
Hey, I'm starting to get
the hang of this game.

02:26.550 --> 02:27.861
The blerns are loaded

02:27.931 --> 02:29.965
the count's three blerns
and two anti-blerns

02:30.033 --> 02:32.586
and the infield blern rule
is in effect. Right?

02:32.655 --> 02:35.550
Except for the word "blern,"
that was complete gibberish.

02:35.620 --> 02:37.103
[ Crowd Gasps ]

02:40.275 --> 02:41.310
[ Cheering ]

02:41.378 --> 02:42.965
[ Announcer ]
Multi-ball!

02:43.033 --> 02:44.620
Multi-ball!

02:47.310 --> 02:49.171
Blern!

02:49.240 --> 02:56.688
Bler-r-r-rn!

02:58.826 --> 03:01.586
All right! Yes!

03:01.655 --> 03:05.033
Miller's on a pace
to hit 70 blerns.

03:05.103 --> 03:08.550
He's good all right, but
he's no Clem Johnson.

03:08.620 --> 03:11.103
And Johnson played
back in the days

03:11.171 --> 03:12.896
before steroid injections
were mandatory.

03:12.965 --> 03:14.655
Clem Johnson?!

03:14.723 --> 03:18.378
That sack of skin
wouldn't have lasted one pitch
in the old robot leagues.

03:18.448 --> 03:20.793
Now, wireless
Joe Jackson--

03:20.861 --> 03:23.723
There was a
blern-hitting machine.

03:23.793 --> 03:26.516
Exactly, he was a machine
designed to hit blerns.

03:26.586 --> 03:28.793
I mean, come on,
wireless Joe was nothing

03:28.861 --> 03:30.516
but a programmable bat
on wheels.

03:30.586 --> 03:32.793
Oh, and I suppose
pitch-o-mat 5000

03:32.861 --> 03:34.723
was just a modified howitzer.

03:34.793 --> 03:36.103
You know, you humans

03:36.171 --> 03:38.688
are so scared
of a little robot competition

03:38.758 --> 03:40.793
you won't even let us
on the field.

03:40.861 --> 03:43.550
There's all kinds
of robots down there.

03:43.620 --> 03:45.481
Yeah. Doing crap work.

03:45.550 --> 03:49.413
They're bat boys, ball
polishers, sprinkler systems

03:49.481 --> 03:52.275
but how many robot managers
are there?

03:52.343 --> 03:53.000
Eleven?

03:53.067 --> 03:54.413
Zero!

03:54.481 --> 03:56.240
And what a surprise.

03:56.310 --> 03:59.103
Look who's scraping up
the filth.

03:59.171 --> 04:01.033
Is it a human child?

04:01.103 --> 04:02.758
I wish.

04:02.826 --> 04:04.448
Whoa! Dear Lord!

04:04.516 --> 04:05.655
What's wrong?

04:05.723 --> 04:09.137
Oh, uh, it's...
my... new pager.

04:09.205 --> 04:11.310
[ Beeping ]

04:11.378 --> 04:12.378
This is Hermes.

04:12.448 --> 04:13.758
A package just came in.

04:13.826 --> 04:16.550
Everyone needs to return
to the office immediately.

04:16.620 --> 04:18.793
[ Groaning ]

04:20.000 --> 04:21.862
Get away, you filthy bird.

04:21.930 --> 04:22.862
Shoo! Shoo!

04:22.930 --> 04:24.862
Professor,
turn me off quick.

04:24.930 --> 04:26.379
I'm sorry. What?

04:26.447 --> 04:27.620
[ Screaming ]

04:27.689 --> 04:30.240
See you at the office.

04:30.310 --> 04:32.137
[ Bender ]
Admit it.

04:32.206 --> 04:34.310
You all think robots
are just machines

04:34.379 --> 04:36.550
built by humans to make
their lives easier.

04:36.620 --> 04:37.723
Well, aren't they?

04:37.793 --> 04:40.274
I've never made
anyone's life easier

04:40.343 --> 04:41.516
and you know it.

04:41.586 --> 04:42.896
Great news,
everyone.

04:42.965 --> 04:46.172
You'll be delivering
a package to Chapek 9--

04:46.240 --> 04:48.826
A world where humans
are killed on sight.

04:48.896 --> 04:50.550
Why is that great news?

04:50.620 --> 04:53.447
I'm glad you asked
that question, Fry.

04:53.516 --> 04:56.826
You see, Chapek 9
was colonized centuries ago

04:56.896 --> 05:00.379
by a murderous crew
of radical robot separatists.

05:00.447 --> 05:03.343
Oh, so just 'cause a robot
wants to kill humans

05:03.413 --> 05:05.067
that makes him a "radical."

05:05.137 --> 05:08.137
Hey, hold on.
I understand these
robots hate humans

05:08.206 --> 05:10.654
but how do they feel
about humanoid aliens?

05:10.723 --> 05:12.481
They're not fans.

05:12.550 --> 05:15.067
That's why Bender
will have to make
the actual delivery.

05:15.137 --> 05:19.103
Oh, I get it--
make the robot do all the work.

05:19.172 --> 05:20.793
This is the first
actual work

05:20.862 --> 05:22.586
you've ever had
to do around here.

05:22.654 --> 05:24.447
Well, I'm not doing it.

05:24.516 --> 05:25.930
It's a robot holiday.

05:26.000 --> 05:27.137
Really? Which one?

05:27.206 --> 05:28.550
Only Robanukah--

05:28.620 --> 05:31.413
The holiest two weeks
on the robot calendar.

05:31.481 --> 05:33.067
Oh, come on, Bender.

05:33.137 --> 05:37.137
Last month it was Robamadan,
and before that Robanzaa.

05:37.206 --> 05:39.206
Man, that one was a blast.

05:39.274 --> 05:40.826
It wasn't just a blast.

05:40.896 --> 05:44.067
It was a sacred tribute
to my ancestral prototypes

05:44.137 --> 05:47.481
which happened to take the form
of a drinking contest.

05:47.550 --> 05:50.310
Now, look here, Bender,
I respect your diversity

05:50.379 --> 05:52.067
to the extent the law requires

05:52.137 --> 05:54.000
but you used up
all your days off

05:54.067 --> 05:56.310
when you had
that bout with roberculosis.

05:56.379 --> 05:59.067
Aw, all right, I'll go,
but so help me

05:59.137 --> 06:03.172
I'll hold a grudge against
every last stinking one of you

06:03.240 --> 06:05.137
for the rest of your lives.

06:05.206 --> 06:06.654
Well, then it's settled.

06:06.723 --> 06:09.137
So long, everyone.

06:10.310 --> 06:12.172
So, let me get this straight.

06:12.240 --> 06:15.379
This planet is
completely uninhabited?No.

06:15.447 --> 06:17.964
It's inhabited by robots.

06:18.033 --> 06:20.862
Oh, kind of like
how a warehouse is
inhabited by boxes.

06:20.930 --> 06:21.896
[ Grumbles ]

06:23.413 --> 06:24.516
Okay, Bender

06:24.586 --> 06:25.654
we're here.

06:25.723 --> 06:27.033
It's time to get to work.

06:27.103 --> 06:29.172
Yes, Miz Leela,
tote that space barge

06:29.240 --> 06:31.103
lift that space bale.

06:31.172 --> 06:32.723
Now, we can't land
on the surface

06:32.793 --> 06:34.862
because those robots
would kill Fry and me.

06:34.930 --> 06:36.862
So, we'll have
to stay up here

06:36.930 --> 06:38.757
and lower you
with the winch.

06:38.826 --> 06:40.723
Remember, you
don't know humans

06:40.793 --> 06:42.343
you don't work
for humans

06:42.413 --> 06:44.723
and above all, you
don't likehumans.

06:44.793 --> 06:46.723
I'll try to keep
that in mind.

06:49.172 --> 06:51.896
Hmm, he seems
pretty angry.

06:51.965 --> 06:54.067
Yeah, but I guess
I'd be kind of angry, too

06:54.137 --> 06:56.067
if I had to go
to some uninhabited planet.

06:56.137 --> 06:58.103
Maybe we ought to do
something nice for him.

07:00.274 --> 07:04.137
There, this oughta show
that stupid robot
we care about him.

07:04.206 --> 07:05.447
[ Electronic Crackle ]

07:05.516 --> 07:07.206
Ah, Bender must be done
with the delivery.

07:08.379 --> 07:09.274
I...

07:09.343 --> 07:10.654
I'm in trouble.

07:10.723 --> 07:13.000
They found out I work
with humans, and--

07:13.067 --> 07:14.137
Oh no. Oh no!

07:14.206 --> 07:15.964
[ Screaming ]

07:16.033 --> 07:17.654
[ Static ]Oh, my God.

07:17.723 --> 07:20.379
We have to go down
and rescue him.No, we can't.

07:20.447 --> 07:21.586
They'll kill us
on sight.

07:21.654 --> 07:22.964
W-W-What are we
going to do?

07:23.033 --> 07:26.343
I don't know. I don't know.
It's not
an easy decision.

07:26.413 --> 07:29.343
If only I had
two or three minutes
to think about it.

07:32.757 --> 07:36.103
If we're going to save Bender
we've got to look and act
exactly like robots.

07:36.172 --> 07:38.137
I am fully operational,
Captain.

07:38.206 --> 07:40.723
We'll have to
walk like robots
talk like robots,

07:40.793 --> 07:44.481
and if necessary
solve complex differential
equations like robots.

07:44.550 --> 07:47.033
I can sort of dance
like a robot.
Will that help?

07:51.343 --> 07:54.240
Oh, Fry, first of all,
this is serious.

07:54.310 --> 07:55.481
And second of all--

08:09.930 --> 08:11.240
Man, we look stupid.

08:11.310 --> 08:14.000
We should have gotten
store-bought costumes.

08:14.067 --> 08:16.757
Yeah, but there wasn't
a Woolworth's in this quadrant.

08:16.826 --> 08:17.689
[ Male ]
Halt!

08:17.757 --> 08:20.723
Be you robot or human?

08:20.793 --> 08:23.310
Robot... we be.

08:23.379 --> 08:24.413
Uh, yep.

08:24.481 --> 08:26.930
Just two robots
out roboting it up.

08:29.067 --> 08:29.930
Eh?

08:30.000 --> 08:32.826
Administer the test.

08:35.136 --> 08:38.620
Which of the following
would you most prefer:

08:38.688 --> 08:39.724
A, a puppy

08:39.793 --> 08:42.481
B, a pretty flower
from your sweetie

08:42.551 --> 08:45.793
or C, a large
properly formatted data file?

08:45.861 --> 08:46.826
Choose!

08:46.895 --> 08:49.793
[ Both Whispering ]

08:49.861 --> 08:52.102
Uh, is the puppy
mechanical
in any way?

08:52.172 --> 08:55.172
No, it is the bad
kind of puppy.

08:55.240 --> 08:56.931
Then we'll go
with that data file.

08:57.000 --> 08:58.206
Correct.

08:58.274 --> 08:59.965
The flower would also
have been acceptable.

09:00.033 --> 09:01.481
You may pass.

09:07.931 --> 09:11.102
[ Leela ]
Now, if you see any robots
just stay out of their way.

09:14.895 --> 09:15.447
[ Gasp ]

09:17.379 --> 09:20.654
[ Leela And Fry
Grunting And Groaning ]

09:25.793 --> 09:27.172
[ Leela ]
So far, so good.

09:29.274 --> 09:31.033
Little to the right...
there you go.

09:31.102 --> 09:33.481
Have you seen this robot?

09:35.000 --> 09:36.793
Sorry, can't
help you.

09:36.861 --> 09:37.965
Hey, watch it!

09:38.033 --> 09:40.344
Don't drop that there.

09:40.413 --> 09:41.620
Oh...

09:44.758 --> 09:46.826
Come on, Fry,
walk like a robot.

09:46.895 --> 09:49.481
I can't. I have to go
to the bathroom.

09:49.551 --> 09:51.102
Robots don't
have bathrooms.

09:51.172 --> 09:52.274
Oh, right.

09:52.344 --> 09:54.240
I wonder where they smoke
in high school?

09:54.309 --> 09:56.447
Listen, just go behind
those garbage cans.

09:56.517 --> 09:57.688
I'll stand guard.

09:57.758 --> 09:59.861
[ Zipper Being Undone ]

09:59.931 --> 10:02.895
[ Humming ]

10:02.965 --> 10:04.654
Hurry up, Fry.

10:04.724 --> 10:05.895
[ Sigh Of Relief ]

10:05.965 --> 10:07.000
Sir, are you aware

10:07.067 --> 10:09.033
that you're
leaking coolant

10:09.102 --> 10:11.379
at an alarming rate?Uh...

10:11.447 --> 10:13.758
Let me just
patch you up
with some hot resin.

10:13.826 --> 10:17.274
I think the leak's
stopping itself.

10:17.344 --> 10:18.586
Wait... wait.

10:18.654 --> 10:21.136
Yeah... there we go.

10:21.206 --> 10:22.724
Wait... yeah.

10:22.793 --> 10:24.136
What sort of robot

10:24.206 --> 10:27.274
turns down a free blast
of searing hot resin?

10:27.344 --> 10:28.379
Uh...

10:28.447 --> 10:30.033
I'm sorry, uh,
my friend and I

10:30.102 --> 10:32.724
have to go perform
some mindless repetitive tasks.

10:32.793 --> 10:36.517
Oh... sounds like
a romantic evening.

10:36.586 --> 10:38.206
I won't keep you.

10:39.620 --> 10:40.931
[ Sneezes ]

10:42.861 --> 10:44.826
[ Electronic Scream ]

10:50.586 --> 10:52.206
Get the humanoid.

10:52.274 --> 10:53.758
Get the intruder.

10:53.826 --> 10:56.240
Intruder alert!
Intruder alert!

10:59.758 --> 11:01.274
Quick, let's
duck in here.

11:02.344 --> 11:03.758
[ Panting ]

11:10.033 --> 11:11.447
[ Man ]
We interrupt this sound file

11:11.517 --> 11:13.344
to bring you a terrifying
announcement.

11:13.413 --> 11:15.758
A non-metallic being
has been sighted

11:15.826 --> 11:17.861
in the vicinity
of make-out point.

11:19.136 --> 11:22.344
Say, Wendy, your chassis
is a little scuffed.

11:22.413 --> 11:24.274
Mind if I polish
it for you?

11:25.826 --> 11:26.793
[ Rustling ]

11:26.861 --> 11:28.481
Did you hear that, Rusty?

11:28.551 --> 11:30.000
It sounded
like a human.

11:30.067 --> 11:31.517
Relax, Wendy.

11:31.586 --> 11:34.033
Humans will never come
to our defenseless
little town.

11:34.102 --> 11:36.172
It's perfectly safe
to let our guard down--

11:36.240 --> 11:37.413
Even for a second.

11:37.481 --> 11:40.758
[ Growling ]

11:42.826 --> 11:44.620
[ Screaming ]

11:46.344 --> 11:52.447
I will eat and digest you all
with my system of mighty organs.

11:52.517 --> 11:54.274
Behold!

11:54.344 --> 11:55.688
[ All Gasping ]

11:55.758 --> 11:57.895
Wow! The 3-D's great!

11:57.965 --> 11:59.826
Mine's not working.

12:05.861 --> 12:07.067
Funny, isn't it?

12:07.136 --> 12:08.965
The human was impervious

12:09.033 --> 12:11.758
to our most powerful
magnetic fields

12:11.826 --> 12:16.274
yet in the end, he succumbed
to a harmless sharpened stick.

12:16.344 --> 12:18.413
[ Chuckling ]

12:20.274 --> 12:22.965
I'm just glad
the nightmare
is over.

12:23.033 --> 12:24.793
It'll never be
over, Wendy.

12:24.861 --> 12:26.965
Even now, humans are lurking
in our playgrounds

12:27.033 --> 12:31.551
our breezeways...
perhaps even...
our movie theaters.

12:31.620 --> 12:33.000
[ All Gasping ]

12:33.067 --> 12:34.067
God help us!

12:36.895 --> 12:39.481
Okay, keep an eye out
for Bender.

12:39.551 --> 12:41.379
So what did
you think of
the movie?

12:41.447 --> 12:42.688
Uh... too much
romance

12:42.758 --> 12:44.206
not enough
human killing.

12:44.274 --> 12:46.206
Yeah, it was
a real chick flick.

12:46.274 --> 12:47.447
[ Siren Wailing ]

12:47.517 --> 12:49.309
What's that?

12:49.379 --> 12:51.000
What do you mean, what's that?

12:51.067 --> 12:52.067
It's 5:00

12:52.136 --> 12:54.102
time for the daily
human hunt.

12:54.172 --> 12:55.344
[ Angry Murmuring ]

12:55.413 --> 12:57.172
Try to stay with the crowd

12:57.240 --> 12:59.688
so no one notices
how crummy you look.

12:59.758 --> 13:01.344
Aw, that was
uncalled for.

13:01.413 --> 13:02.724
I'm over here.

13:02.793 --> 13:06.067
[ Murmuring ]

13:06.136 --> 13:08.447
I heard a human was
draining coolant

13:08.517 --> 13:09.965
behind garbage can 738.

13:10.033 --> 13:12.688
I heard they unscrew
our lug nuts at night

13:12.758 --> 13:15.000
and eat them
at their human brunches.

13:15.067 --> 13:17.481
Welcome to a very special
human hunt.

13:17.551 --> 13:19.517
We have with us today
a guest

13:19.586 --> 13:21.758
whose irrational hatred
for humans

13:21.826 --> 13:24.240
makes me look like
a human sympathizer.

13:24.309 --> 13:26.033
[ All Laughing ]

13:26.102 --> 13:28.654
A newly arrived refugee
from earth--

13:28.724 --> 13:30.481
Let's hear it for Bender!

13:30.551 --> 13:31.826
[ Applause ]

13:33.172 --> 13:34.826
It's him.
He's okay.

13:34.895 --> 13:37.481
Death to humans!

13:37.551 --> 13:39.344
[ Cheering ]

13:39.413 --> 13:42.931
Ah, it's good
to hear his voice.

13:45.447 --> 13:48.586
Many said I was too extreme
when I first called

13:48.654 --> 13:51.654
for the annihilation
of the human species

13:51.724 --> 13:54.793
as well as some
of the more cunning monkeys

13:54.861 --> 13:56.379
but after living on earth

13:56.447 --> 14:01.551
I can tell you that I am,
if anything, too merciful.

14:01.620 --> 14:04.481
[ Cheering And Hooting ]

14:04.551 --> 14:07.206
My God, he's
become evil.

14:07.274 --> 14:09.136
I mean, eviller.

14:09.206 --> 14:10.620
Thank you. Thank you.

14:10.688 --> 14:12.826
And if you enjoyed that diatribe

14:12.895 --> 14:16.067
then you'll want to purchase
my spoken-word album.

14:16.136 --> 14:18.033
Just $18.95.

14:18.102 --> 14:21.758
Act now and you'll get
this Bender action figurine.

14:21.826 --> 14:24.033
Bite my shiny
metal ass.

14:24.102 --> 14:25.344
Got to have it!
Right here!

14:25.413 --> 14:26.793
Over here!

14:26.861 --> 14:30.000
Let the hunt begin!

14:30.067 --> 14:32.344
[ Playing Mechanical Fanfare ]

14:32.413 --> 14:33.895
[ Growling And Murmuring ]

14:36.274 --> 14:38.206
[ Curious Murmurs ]

14:38.274 --> 14:40.206
[ Disappointed Murmurs ]

14:40.274 --> 14:43.826
Now, your basic human is between
three and 25 feet tall

14:43.895 --> 14:47.033
and is made of a hairy, oily goo
wrapped in a T-shirt.

14:47.102 --> 14:48.379
Is it true
they bite your neck

14:48.447 --> 14:49.826
and suck your
transmission fluid

14:49.895 --> 14:51.102
and then you become
a human?

14:51.172 --> 14:52.620
Sure, why not.

14:52.688 --> 14:54.206
Anything in the trap?

14:54.274 --> 14:55.793
Nothing.

14:55.861 --> 14:58.793
Today's active humans
prefer a low-calorie bait.

14:58.861 --> 15:02.551
Well, that makes 146,000
unsuccessful hunts in a row

15:02.620 --> 15:05.551
but I've got a good
feeling about tomorrow.

15:05.620 --> 15:08.517
[ Bender ]
Wait.
What's that?

15:08.586 --> 15:11.033
Oh, that's the
old, abandoned
adult bookstore.

15:11.102 --> 15:12.931
Nothing in there,
except maybe

15:13.000 --> 15:15.688
a few shreds of moldy,
old robot pornography.

15:15.758 --> 15:17.517
Hmm.

15:17.586 --> 15:19.620
Sounds like a breeding ground
for humans.

15:19.688 --> 15:22.586
I better check it out.

15:22.654 --> 15:24.620
Oh, yeah.

15:24.688 --> 15:28.206
You're a bad girl,
aren't you?

15:28.274 --> 15:29.481
Psst! Bender.

15:29.551 --> 15:30.895
Wha-what?

15:30.965 --> 15:31.965
Oh, you?!

15:32.033 --> 15:33.447
What the hell are
you doing here?

15:33.517 --> 15:35.067
We've been looking for you.

15:35.136 --> 15:38.826
Last we heard, you were under
arrest as a human sympathizer.

15:38.895 --> 15:41.000
I was-- but they let me go
when I told them

15:41.067 --> 15:42.654
I killed
a million billion humans.

15:42.724 --> 15:43.826
Good for you.

15:43.895 --> 15:45.240
Now, let's all get
back to the ship.

15:45.309 --> 15:46.274
What for?

15:46.344 --> 15:47.413
We're rescuing you.

15:47.481 --> 15:49.033
I don't want to be rescued.

15:49.102 --> 15:49.654
Say what?

15:49.724 --> 15:51.724
I love this planet.

15:51.793 --> 15:53.309
I've got wealth, fame

15:53.379 --> 15:56.379
and access
to the depths of sleaze
that those things bring.

15:56.447 --> 15:58.413
But, Bender,
we're your friends.

15:58.481 --> 16:01.758
Friends? That activates
my hilarity unit.

16:01.826 --> 16:03.274
I'm just
a machine to you.

16:03.344 --> 16:04.965
You're no more
friends with me

16:05.033 --> 16:06.620
than you are
with the toaster

16:06.688 --> 16:08.895
or the phonograph,
or the electric chair.

16:08.965 --> 16:10.240
That's not true.

16:10.309 --> 16:12.895
Well, that's
how it feels to me.

16:17.379 --> 16:18.861
Bye, Bender.
I'll miss you.

16:18.931 --> 16:20.551
Oh, go on.

16:20.620 --> 16:22.586
Get out of here
before you get caught.

16:22.654 --> 16:24.344
[ Mayor ]
Bender, good news.

16:24.413 --> 16:26.033
Your album just
went gold.

16:26.102 --> 16:27.136
What the...?

16:27.206 --> 16:28.240
It's the humans!

16:28.309 --> 16:30.102
[ Robots Gasping ]

16:30.172 --> 16:32.000
Bender, do something!

16:33.206 --> 16:36.551
Got you, you murderous
flesh-piles.

16:39.861 --> 16:41.861
Your honor, I intend
to demonstrate

16:41.931 --> 16:44.586
beyond 0.5 percent of a doubt

16:44.654 --> 16:46.274
that these humans
before us

16:46.344 --> 16:48.793
are guilty of the crime
of being humans.

16:48.861 --> 16:51.309
Come to think of it,
I rest may case.

16:51.379 --> 16:52.724
Thank you, prosecutor.

16:52.793 --> 16:55.102
I will now consider
the evidence.

16:56.551 --> 16:57.758
Hey, wait a minute.

16:57.826 --> 16:59.309
Isn't anyone going
to defend us?

16:59.379 --> 17:01.965
Yeah. I mean, he may not
have a case

17:02.033 --> 17:04.103
but I'm genuinely not
a human.

17:04.172 --> 17:05.448
Quiet, human!

17:08.240 --> 17:09.240
Uh-oh.

17:09.309 --> 17:10.550
He froze up again.

17:10.619 --> 17:12.172
Try control-alt-delete.

17:12.240 --> 17:13.619
Jiggle the cord.

17:13.689 --> 17:14.826
Turn him off and on.

17:14.895 --> 17:16.205
Clean the gunk
out of the mouse.

17:16.275 --> 17:17.826
Call technical support.

17:17.895 --> 17:19.862
Okay, okay,
he's back on-line.

17:21.275 --> 17:23.931
I find the defendants guilty.

17:24.000 --> 17:25.862
[ Robots Cheering ]

17:25.931 --> 17:28.723
No!Look, one eye.

17:28.792 --> 17:31.103
Count them: one.
Not human.

17:31.172 --> 17:35.378
The humans are hereby sentenced
to live as robots live on earth.

17:35.448 --> 17:37.689
They will perform
tedious calculations

17:37.758 --> 17:39.205
and spot-weld
automobiles

17:39.275 --> 17:40.758
until they become
obsolete

17:40.826 --> 17:43.654
and are given away
to an inner-city
middle school.

17:43.723 --> 17:45.826
[ All Cheering ]

17:45.895 --> 17:47.205
Great work,
Bender.

17:47.275 --> 17:50.448
You've taught us
to hate humans
all over again.

17:50.517 --> 17:51.654
[ Laughing ]

17:51.723 --> 17:53.172
[ Groaning ]

17:54.792 --> 17:55.689
[ Screaming ]

17:55.758 --> 17:57.205
[ Both Grunting ]

17:57.275 --> 17:58.275
Are you all right?

17:58.344 --> 17:59.275
Oh, yeah.

17:59.344 --> 18:00.309
[ Gasping ]

18:00.378 --> 18:02.309
Who are you?

18:02.378 --> 18:03.758
We are the robot elders.

18:03.826 --> 18:05.481
You don't look very old.

18:05.550 --> 18:08.344
Thanks.
We try to take care
of ourselves.

18:08.413 --> 18:09.448
What's going on here?

18:09.517 --> 18:11.862
Silence! Bring in Bender.

18:13.550 --> 18:14.895
Uh, let's make this quick.

18:14.964 --> 18:17.413
I'm due at the opening
of a mini-mall.

18:17.481 --> 18:18.586
Hey! What is this?

18:18.654 --> 18:20.103
Silence.

18:20.172 --> 18:21.723
It is time to put the humans
to death.

18:21.792 --> 18:23.136
[ Both Gasping ]

18:23.205 --> 18:25.067
But the judge
already sentenced
us at the trial.

18:25.136 --> 18:27.136
Silence.

18:27.205 --> 18:29.067
That was just a show
for the public.

18:29.136 --> 18:31.205
We are the true rulers
of this planet.

18:31.275 --> 18:33.826
Hand-carved from meteorites
by the robot founders

18:33.895 --> 18:35.205
over four centuries ago.

18:35.275 --> 18:37.344
Silence! Come forward, Bender.

18:37.413 --> 18:40.205
You will have the honor of
executing the prisoners.

18:40.275 --> 18:42.136
Silence! I concur.

18:42.205 --> 18:45.034
Here...
use the ceremonial
killamajig.

18:47.586 --> 18:49.103
[ Startled Yelp ]

18:49.172 --> 18:52.034
Uh... I'm a little
tired right now.

18:52.103 --> 18:55.309
Would it be all right
if I just gave them
a savage beating?

18:55.378 --> 18:58.103
No! The elders
have spoken.

18:58.172 --> 19:00.205
Show us the killing skills

19:00.275 --> 19:02.103
that have made you
a media darling.

19:02.172 --> 19:03.586
Do it now.

19:03.654 --> 19:05.826
Kill them before they bring down
our whole society.

19:05.895 --> 19:08.067
[ Elders Chanting ]
Do it. Do it. Do it.

19:08.136 --> 19:10.413
Do it. Do it. Do it. Do it.

19:10.481 --> 19:12.275
Do it. Do it. Do it.

19:12.344 --> 19:14.481
Do it. Do it. Do it.

19:14.550 --> 19:17.103
Oh...

19:17.172 --> 19:18.792
[ All Gasping ]

19:18.862 --> 19:20.517
I can't kill them.

19:20.586 --> 19:23.964
Plenty of humans have
mistreated robots

19:24.034 --> 19:25.550
but not these two.

19:25.619 --> 19:27.448
They're my friends.

19:27.517 --> 19:29.931
Humans are no
threat to us.

19:30.000 --> 19:32.792
They're stupid,
putrid cowards.

19:32.862 --> 19:34.826
Damn right!

19:34.895 --> 19:38.723
The fact is, humans are
completely harmless.

19:38.792 --> 19:40.413
We're well aware of that.

19:40.481 --> 19:41.448
You are?

19:41.517 --> 19:43.205
Of course.

19:43.275 --> 19:45.000
But they're useful
to us as a scapegoat

19:45.067 --> 19:47.172
to distract the public
from their real problems.

19:47.240 --> 19:49.481
Like our crippling
lug nut shortage.

19:49.550 --> 19:52.103
And a corrupt government
of incompetent robot elders.

19:52.172 --> 19:54.309
Duh... that's for sure.

19:54.378 --> 19:55.448
Quiet, Jimmy.

19:55.517 --> 19:58.517
Well, I'm glad we got
all that out in the open.

19:58.586 --> 20:00.309
We'll just let
ourselves out.

20:00.378 --> 20:02.378
Silence! You all know too much.

20:02.448 --> 20:07.550
Elders, execute function
control-shift-kill.

20:10.689 --> 20:12.136
Stop!

20:12.205 --> 20:14.689
Take one more step
and I'll breathe
fire on you!

20:15.931 --> 20:17.895
He'll do it.
He's crazy.

20:17.964 --> 20:19.413
Can they really
breathe fire

20:19.481 --> 20:20.654
or did we make that up?

20:20.723 --> 20:22.689
Gee, I can't remember
anymore.

20:22.758 --> 20:25.378
It might just be
from that stupid movie.

20:25.448 --> 20:27.448
Was that original
or the remake?

20:27.517 --> 20:28.550
I don't...

20:28.619 --> 20:29.895
Hey! They're getting away!

20:31.654 --> 20:33.413
[ Panting ]

20:39.586 --> 20:40.586
Yep.

20:40.654 --> 20:42.240
So long, suckers.

20:42.309 --> 20:44.895
Uh... hello, suckers.

20:46.344 --> 20:47.550
Hey, hold on a second.

20:47.619 --> 20:49.448
I forgot to deliver
the package.

20:49.517 --> 20:51.448
[ All ]
Whoa!

20:53.240 --> 20:55.000
[ Pained Groans And Grunts ]

20:59.964 --> 21:03.344
Lug nuts! Precious lug nuts!

21:03.413 --> 21:05.654
Hooray for the humans!

21:08.034 --> 21:10.792
Wow, I can't believe you guys
did all this for me.

21:10.862 --> 21:13.378
This is the best Robanukah ever.

21:13.448 --> 21:17.034
We wanted to show you
that we really do respect
your robot heritage.

21:17.103 --> 21:19.481
Aw, thanks.

21:19.550 --> 21:22.758
You do know
that I made Robanukah up
to get out of work, right?

21:22.826 --> 21:24.172
Of course.

21:24.240 --> 21:26.586
But that doesn't make it
any less meaningful.

21:26.654 --> 21:27.964
In that case...

21:28.034 --> 21:30.517
let the dancing begin!

21:30.586 --> 21:32.550
[ Music Playing ]

21:38.481 --> 21:40.550
Hey, you guys are good.

21:40.619 --> 21:42.517
How the hell do you do that?
